<bug>
    <id>3945</id>
    <title>Media: Unable to use photos from library when camera permission has been denied.</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">To reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">- From a fresh install open the editor and tap to add media to a post.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.3">- When prompted to allow access to the camera, tap deny.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.4">- When prmopted to allow access to the library, allow.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">My expectation is WordPress won't have access to my camera but will still be able to pull media from the phone's gallery, or the blog's media library.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">Instead I see an error message saying that permission is needed.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
